(5, 'Technology Practice Lead, Infrastructure Modernization, Google Cloud', '• Experience leading and managing a team to thrive in ambiguity in a dynamic, highly matrixed environment.\r\n• Knowledge of cloud technology and architectures\r\n• Ability to collaborate effectively across organizational boundaries, build relationships, and import and export talent and ideas to achieve a broader organizational goal.\r\n• Excellent presentation skills, with the ability to deliver a polished and professional business and technical pitch to the C-Suite and Board levels.', 'Build, inspire, and lead a cross-functional distributed practice of specialist Customer Engineers across the sub region.\r\nBe the external voice of Google Cloud for your specialist focus area which includes press and analyst communities, customers and partners.\r\nReflect the voice of the Regional customers, partners, and field to influence a data-driven vision and direction for technology, solutions, and use case development at Google Cloud.\r\nAssist in the delivery of published materials aligned to your specific specialist focus area supporting Google Cloud solutions and use cases.\r\nPartner closely with Customer Engineering leader, Product leaders, Sales strategy, and executive leadership to ensure solutions alignment with engineering, product priorities, and go-to-market priorities.', 'Assist in the delivery of published materials aligned to your specific specialist focus area supporting Google Cloud solutions and use cases.\r\nPartner closely with Customer Engineering leader, Product leaders, Sales strategy, and executive leadership to ensure solutions alignment with engineering, product priorities, and go-to-market priorities.\r\nAssist in the delivery of published materials aligned to your specific specialist focus area supporting Google Cloud solutions and use cases.\r\nPartner closely with Customer Engineering leader, Product leaders, Sales strategy, and executive leadership to ensure solutions 